The paper deals with the design of LDPC codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the study of equal-capacity channels and their convex combinations, which falls under the category of coding theory (cs.CC). The paper proposes a method for decomposing symmetric channels, which is related to network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of LDPC codes across a multitude of channels, which could be considered a topic in data science (cs.DS).
